1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:03,250
I'm Kosuke Maruya from the sales department.

2
00:00:03,250 --> 00:00:05,370
I am you.

3
00:00:05,370 --> 00:00:08,690
I am the 59-year-old Kosuke Maruya.

4
00:00:08,690 --> 00:00:11,550
I come from 30 years in the future.

5
00:00:11,550 --> 00:00:14,990
After the future me proclaimed that my cuteness would not last long,

6
00:00:14,990 --> 00:00:17,670
my life began to take a drastic turn for the worse.

7
00:00:18,990 --> 00:00:21,190
You look terrible.

8
00:00:21,190 --> 00:00:25,160
And she appeared before me at this time.

9
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:27,200
Sanada-san!

10
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,900
I've fallen in love with you.

11
00:00:30,830 --> 00:00:32,850
This is the first time...

12
00:00:32,850 --> 00:00:35,390
This is the first time I fell in love and confessed.

13
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:37,260
However...

14
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:39,320
- Sanada-san.
- Izumi!

15
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:43,040
Long time no see.

16
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:45,360
What is your relationship with Izumi Sanada-san?

17
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:48,860
I'm Izumi's older brother, Yamato.

18
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:49,771
What!

19
00:00:49,771 --> 00:00:52,690
The HR consultant who stepped in during the company's crisis

20
00:00:52,690 --> 00:00:55,080
was her twin brother.

21
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,670
The Georgia Brewery over in America

22
00:00:57,670 --> 00:01:00,300
is starting up a new research institute,

23
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:02,450
and they're hiring new researchers.

24
00:01:02,450 --> 00:01:04,430
You have no idea how I feel.

25
00:01:04,430 --> 00:01:07,790
But you always pretend like you do, Yamato.

26
00:01:07,790 --> 00:01:10,120
- Sanada-san?
- All I wanted

27
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,690
was to make a place for myself.

28
00:01:12,690 --> 00:01:14,730
Wait, Sanada-san!

29
00:01:14,730 --> 00:01:17,460
If you're carrying a burden,

30
00:01:17,460 --> 00:01:20,290
I'd like to overcome it together.

31
00:01:20,290 --> 00:01:21,890
Why...

32
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:28,050
why am I the only one who has to open up?

33
00:01:28,050 --> 00:01:31,010
- What?
- You didn't tell me the truth, right?

34
00:01:31,010 --> 00:01:33,020
I saw Maruya Brewery's website.

35
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:37,000
The President pictured there is your dad, yes?
[President: Yasuhiro Maruya]

36
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:39,810
Your father just came back.

37
00:01:39,810 --> 00:01:41,290
Hey.

38
00:01:43,330 --> 00:01:46,290
- Oh.
- Then who was the person I met?

39
00:01:46,290 --> 00:01:47,980
Why did you lie?

40
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:50,810
- B-Becauseâ€”
- I...

41
00:01:52,260 --> 00:01:55,190
knew nothing about you.

42
00:01:59,290 --> 00:02:01,190
Sanada-san!

43
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,700
All right, that's enough.

44
00:02:04,620 --> 00:02:07,970
You've now reached your expiration date.

45
00:02:07,970 --> 00:02:10,480
- "Expiration date"?
- Yes.

46
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:13,020
It's your thirtieth birthday in eight days.

47
00:02:13,020 --> 00:02:14,950
That's your expiration date.

48
00:02:14,950 --> 00:02:16,910
If you want me to be even clearer,

49
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:19,450
that day is the end of your cuteness.

50
00:02:20,230 --> 00:02:21,840
Even if that's true,

51
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,960
so what?

52
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,090
It's pointless.

53
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:26,620
Even if you follow her now,

54
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:30,840
I, your future self, am not with Izumi Sanada.

55
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:34,550
The future will not change.

56
00:02:35,970 --> 00:02:39,150
My cuteness is about to expire.

57
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:44,250
And 30 years later, I'm not with Sanada-san.

58
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:49,840
What is this?

59
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:55,890
Did you come from the future just to tell me this?

60
00:02:57,810 --> 00:03:00,880
Don't interfere with the past, okay?

61
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:11,540
The future me has no right to get in the way of the current me!

62
00:03:20,930 --> 00:03:22,970
You're right.

63
00:03:40,350 --> 00:03:42,800
[Izumi Sanada: Can we talk after work today?]

64
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:46,190
She wants to talk...

65
00:03:52,610 --> 00:03:54,280
What does she want to talk about?

66
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:55,600
It worries me.

67
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:58,990
She's so close, yet I can't ask her about it.

68
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,280
She noticed it.

69
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,090
[Kousuke Maruya: What do you want to talk about?]

70
00:04:14,210 --> 00:04:15,540
She read it, but didn't reply.

71
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:18,210
Why? What's happening?

72
00:04:18,210 --> 00:04:21,370
Everyone, can I have your attention, please?

73
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:27,840
Good morning.

74
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,770
Good morning.

75
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:33,370
Regarding the current situation of Yayoi Beer,

76
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:35,410
there are rumors of a merger.

77
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:37,910
However, I personally believe the best strategy

78
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:40,120
is to explore a self-sustaining restructuring plan.

79
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:45,160
However, we must continue to streamline management.

80
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:47,050
As part of this...

81
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:53,340
We are considering restructuring and removing the sales department and branch offices.

82
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:54,880
What?

83
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,170
"Restructuring and removing the sales department"?

84
00:04:57,170 --> 00:04:58,910
Restructure and removal?

85
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:01,650
How can they be so cruel?

86
00:05:01,650 --> 00:05:03,610
Kaburagi-san...

87
00:05:05,940 --> 00:05:07,480
All right, listen.

88
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:11,740
In line with this, we would also like to offer

89
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:14,650
early retirement packages at the same time.

90
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:20,150
Isn't it too demanding to streamline the sales department?
[Early Retirement Guidelines]

91
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:26,100
That said, I wouldn't dare to quit just like that.
[Izumi Sanada: Can we talk after work today?]

92
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,080
Yes.

93
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,780
It's really tough.

94
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,390
Maruya-kun.

95
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:40,070
You're not thinking about quitting, right?

96
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:41,560
I'm not.

97
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:44,250
This one is fine for now.

98
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:46,140
What's the matter?

99
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:50,700
What's with you, too? You look troubled.

100
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,630
Ichinose, what happened to you?

101
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:53,441
Nothing.

102
00:05:53,441 --> 00:05:55,820
- Stomachache?
- No.

103
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,600
Actually...

104
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,100
I saw it in the hallway earlier.

105
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:05,450
Director, you dropped something.

106
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,200
Thank you.

107
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,870
[Resignation Letter]

108
00:06:11,530 --> 00:06:13,450
"Resignation Letter"?

109
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:18,690
Ichinose-kun, don't tell anyone that I have this.

110
00:06:18,690 --> 00:06:20,120
Okay?

111
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,130
Yes.

112
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:22,250
You've got a big mouth.

113
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:24,550
If it were you, you couldn't keep quiet, either.

114
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:25,900
- That's true.
- Right?

115
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:28,800
So whose resignation letter was that?

116
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:33,400
As for that... I was too shocked and didn't see it.

117
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:37,400
- That was the most important part!
- Sorry.

118
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:40,400
But since the Director was holding on to it...

119
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:44,650
This means someone in our department submitted it, right?

120
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:46,370
You're right.

121
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:56,560
One of these people is leaving the company.

122
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:10,990
[Izumi Sanada: It's something important. I'd like to say it in person.]

123
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:14,810
Don't tell me.

124
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:23,560
was it Sanada-san who submitted the resignation?

125
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:28,100
[Ore no Kawaii wa Mousugu Shohikigen!?]

126
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:32,750
[My Cuteness Is About to Expire!?]

127
00:07:39,700 --> 00:07:41,330
It's only 10 a.m.

128
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:44,590
The workday isn't over for at least six more hours.

129
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:47,340
I'm sure Sanada wishes to work

130
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:49,920
in a research job.

131
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,890
You'd be better off pursuing your passion than staying at Yayoi Beer,

132
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,200
working in a job that doesn't suit you.

133
00:07:56,130 --> 00:07:58,070
[Izumi Sanada: Can we talk after work today?]

134
00:07:58,070 --> 00:08:00,770
So was it Sanada-san who submitted the resignation letter after all?

135
00:08:00,770 --> 00:08:04,130
I really want to know what it is.

136
00:08:04,130 --> 00:08:06,980
But we are working now.

137
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:08,010
I must concentrate.

138
00:08:08,010 --> 00:08:09,400
[Izumi Sanada: Can we talk after work today?]

139
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,240
I just can't.

140
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,820
How about I talk to her about the early retirement package?

141
00:08:13,820 --> 00:08:16,810
Wait, but maybe she wants to talk about the other matter.

142
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:20,500
The President pictured on the website is your dad, yes?
[President: Yasuhiro Maruya]

143
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,910
I am Kosuke Maruya's father.

144
00:08:22,910 --> 00:08:24,820
Then who was the person I met?

145
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:26,590
Why did you lie?

146
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:29,090
Yes. That's more likely to be the case.

147
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:33,020
In any case, I can't help but wonder when we are alone together.

148
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:34,310
Sanada-san.

149
00:08:34,310 --> 00:08:37,130
Regarding the message this morning...

150
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:39,360
What is it you want to talk about?

151
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,750
What is the time now?

152
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:48,820
"Now"? It's 10:13 now.

153
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:51,970
I think it's too early to discuss personal matters.

154
00:08:51,970 --> 00:08:52,970
Right.

155
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:54,060
Well...

156
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:56,160
I know, but...

157
00:08:56,990 --> 00:09:01,870
My mind is muddled, and I can't concentrate on my work at this point.

158
00:09:03,590 --> 00:09:05,160
I got it.

159
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,550
It's early, but we could take a lunch break.

160
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:08,970
Then could we talk?

161
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:11,170
Are you absolutely sure?

162
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:13,810
Yes, please.

163
00:09:15,910 --> 00:09:19,580
I am truly sorry for being so distraught yesterday.

164
00:09:19,580 --> 00:09:22,040
I thought I would first apologize for that.

165
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,990
Oh...

166
00:09:23,990 --> 00:09:25,370
Oh my.

167
00:09:25,370 --> 00:09:28,200
She just wanted to apologize. That's great.

168
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,750
Also, I am truly sorry to say this, but...

169
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:32,900
What is it?

170
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:38,110
I would like to end our romantic relationship today.

171
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:43,330
- What did you say?
- Please end our relationship.

172
00:09:43,330 --> 00:09:45,880
- Do you mean...
- Please break up with me.

173
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:49,320
What?

174
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:51,420
W-Wait... wait a minute.

175
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:53,810
If it's about that old man, I didn't mean to lie to you.

176
00:09:53,810 --> 00:09:56,210
- Many things happened and...
- Regarding that matter,

177
00:09:56,210 --> 00:09:58,180
I'm fine now.

178
00:09:58,180 --> 00:10:00,350
That's not why I want to break up with you.

179
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:01,380
Then why?

180
00:10:01,380 --> 00:10:05,800
I realized that I am unable to date men after all.

181
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:08,670
- But...
- That twice-cooked pork set meal is mine.

182
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:10,680
Sorry to have kept you waiting.

183
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:15,570
The problem lies with me. I hope you'll understand.

184
00:10:15,570 --> 00:10:18,330
Also, I have already informed Director Yamamuro that

185
00:10:18,330 --> 00:10:21,220
I will be taking paid leave for a while starting tomorrow.

186
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:23,300
- What?
- I need some time

187
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:26,000
to sort myself out now.

188
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:28,930
That's all I wanted to tell you.

189
00:10:28,930 --> 00:10:31,180
I will start eating first.

190
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:35,130
How could this be?

191
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:45,840
I shouldn't have asked her about it.

192
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:47,750
I want to cry, but I can't do it now.

193
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:50,400
My mind is a mess, and I can't think straight.

194
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:54,570
Why couldn't I wait until after work?

195
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:56,200
Sanada-san.

196
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,280
I have an appointment after this.

197
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:02,380
Can you go back to the office first?

198
00:11:02,380 --> 00:11:03,450
All right.

199
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:05,390
Excuse me.

200
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:14,410
Even if you follow her now,

201
00:11:14,410 --> 00:11:18,350
I, your future self, am not with Izumi Sanada.

202
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:21,290
The future will not change.

203
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:24,690
In the end, that's what our fate was.

204
00:11:24,690 --> 00:11:28,400
I didn't think it would happen so soon,

205
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,620
just like that.

