00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:43,610
Kosuke!

224
00:12:51,210 --> 00:12:53,080
Hold on.

225
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:56,730
Your face...

226
00:12:56,730 --> 00:12:58,350
Kosuke, your face...

227
00:12:58,350 --> 00:13:00,570
- Many things happened.
- No way!

228
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:13,300
I should soothe my eyes in the restroom.

229
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:18,340
Everyone, can I have a moment, please?

230
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:20,140
Ichinose-kun, what is it?

231
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:21,840
All right, gather over here, everyone.

232
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,220
Come over here.

233
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:25,490
You've grown so much.

234
00:13:25,490 --> 00:13:28,050
Really? Thank you.

235
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:30,400
Maruya-san, can I have some of your time?

236
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,300
Yes.

237
00:13:32,870 --> 00:13:35,320
"Strategy to increase sales by 10%"?

238
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:38,340
Yes, please take a look at this.

239
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:44,120
As long as we increase the head office's performance target by another 10%,

240
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,040
we should be able to resolve the crisis
[Sales Simulation Graph]

241
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:50,140
with this year's estimated business revenue.
[Dangerous Area Line]

242
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:51,820
Do you mean that if it can be achieved,

243
00:13:51,820 --> 00:13:53,500
maybe the management will reconsider

244
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,750
the restructure and removal of the sales department?

245
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:56,621
Yes!

246
00:13:56,621 --> 00:13:58,230
But a 10% increase in sales

247
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:00,620
for all clients is a lot of work.

248
00:14:00,620 --> 00:14:01,900
I know.

249
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:06,720
But we normally serve the sales accounts of large chain stores, don't we?

250
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:11,970
For them, we analyze the sales data and propose a sales plan.

251
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:15,540
I was wondering if we could also do the same for small retailers.

252
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:19,540
Hold on.

253
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:22,140
How many small retailers do you think there are in the entire area?

254
00:14:22,140 --> 00:14:27,300
But by doing this, we might be able to stop the sales department from being restructured.

255
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,380
As long as the possibility isn't zero,

256
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:32,170
I'd like to give it a try.

257
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:37,090
Maruya-san?

258
00:14:38,830 --> 00:14:41,930
Were my feelings conveyed?

259
00:14:41,930 --> 00:14:46,370
- Well...
- Since Maruya-kun was so moved by it,

260
00:14:46,370 --> 00:14:48,400
there's no reason not to do it.

261
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,860
- Right?
- Yes.

262
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:52,310
Yes, let's do it.

263
00:14:52,310 --> 00:14:54,210
- Right?
- Yes.

264
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:56,010
Let's do it.

265
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:57,610
Thank you very much!

266
00:14:57,610 --> 00:15:01,200
If that's the case, we start gathering data on small retailers.

267
00:15:01,210 --> 00:15:04,110
However, we don't have much time. What do we do?

268
00:15:04,110 --> 00:15:07,090
I have an idea about data collection.

269
00:15:16,330 --> 00:15:18,370
This.

270
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:20,630
How nostalgic!

271
00:15:20,630 --> 00:15:21,910
"Empty can notes"?

272
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:25,010
When I was a newbie, I researched discarded beer cans

273
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:27,460
while traveling around Tokyo on sales assignments.
[April-July period: 1-4 Naka-Shinjuku, Shinjuku-ku]

274
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:28,441
[Shop name, trash bin]

275
00:15:28,441 --> 00:15:29,730
Maruya-kun could tell which beer

276
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:32,380
from which company is more popular

277
00:15:32,380 --> 00:15:33,600
by checking empty cans in trash bins.

278
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:36,900
You can observe customers' real thoughts that aren't in the data.

279
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:38,420
Let's do the same this time.

280
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:39,371
No.

281
00:15:39,371 --> 00:15:40,670
This time, I also suggest

282
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:43,620
we provide recycling bins for empty cans

283
00:15:43,620 --> 00:15:46,240
and have them placed in front of the retailers.

284
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,720
I see.

285
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:50,360
I think it's a great idea.

286
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,120
- Right?
- Yes.

287
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,540
Let's do it.

288
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:54,900
Let's do it.

289
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:56,510
Wait a minute.

290
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:59,230
What are you guys trying to do on your own?

291
00:15:59,230 --> 00:16:00,231
Director.

292
00:16:00,231 --> 00:16:02,500
The issue of streamlining the sales department

293
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,670
will be discussed at the upcoming Executive Committee meeting.

294
00:16:04,670 --> 00:16:06,540
- "Executive Committee meeting"?
- Yes.

295
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:08,700
It will be held next week.

296
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:12,510
If you guys can get the new sales plan proposal ready in time,

297
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:14,920
I'll persuade the upper management.

298
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:17,350
Director!

299
00:16:17,350 --> 00:16:18,660
Thank you very much.

300
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,490
Thank you very much.

301
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,170
Well, then

302
00:16:23,170 --> 00:16:25,420
the strategy to increase sales by 10%...

303
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:28,690
- Let's do our best!
- Yes!

304
00:16:28,690 --> 00:16:31,180
- Let's do it!
- Okay!

305
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:42,060
Are you going home?

306
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:43,330
Yes.

307
00:16:43,330 --> 00:16:46,400
As I've said, I will be on leave starting tomorrow.

308
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,630
Got it.

309
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:49,460
Well, then thank you for the hard work today.

310
00:16:49,460 --> 00:16:50,660
I'll be leaving.

311
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:52,430
Thank you for your hard work today.

312
00:16:57,660 --> 00:17:00,950
I wonder if this is the end of us.

313
00:17:00,950 --> 00:17:04,600
In the end, I still don't know what feelings she's hiding in her heart.

314
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,030
No.

315
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:07,870
Even if I knew,

316
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:11,340
there is nothing else

317
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:13,320
I can do for her.

318
00:17:14,730 --> 00:17:16,350
[Empty can recycle campaign guide]

319
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:17,800
What I can do now...

320
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:18,631
Please support us.

321
00:17:18,631 --> 00:17:20,050
I must do something about this first.

322
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:22,350
Since you've made the request, Maruya-kun...

323
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:24,210
All right, place it anywhere you like.

324
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:25,830
Thank you very much.

325
00:17:25,830 --> 00:17:28,750
Can we place this recycle box here?

326
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:30,380
What did you say?

327
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:31,950
A recital?

328
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:33,680
It's "recycle."

329
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,260
Recital.

330
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:37,060
"Recycle!"

331
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:40,200
- R-R-Recital, right?
- That's totally different!

332
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,980
No one will be singing!

333
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:44,470
One, two, three, four, five.

334
00:17:47,940 --> 00:17:50,240
One, two...

335
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:53,260
three, four, five, Yayoi.

336
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:56,750
One, two, three, four, five, Teio.

337
00:17:56,750 --> 00:18:00,010
Three, four...

338
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:04,080
Thank you for the hard work.

339
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,560
Thank you for the hard work.

340
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:14,470
A busy and tired Maruya-kun looks good too.

341
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:16,110
Everyone!

342
00:18:16,110 --> 00:18:19,370
I know everyone is tired,

343
00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:20,840
but how about drinks for motivation?

344
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:22,230
That's a good idea!

345
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:24,240
Thank you!

346
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,540
As our department's senior,

347
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:32,390
I, Kaburagi, would like to propose a toast to this campaign

348
00:18:32,390 --> 00:18:34,830
- to increase sales by 10%...
- Cheers!

349
00:18:34,830 --> 00:18:35,981
Cheers!

350
00:18:35,981 --> 00:18:37,300
Hold on, Ichinose-kun.

351
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:39,670
Cheers.

352
00:18:39,670 --> 00:18:41,450
Cheers.

353
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:43,810
With what happened this time,

354
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:45,870
I see again how amazing you are, Maruya-san.

355
00:18:45,870 --> 00:18:49,180
Salespeople are really good at complimenting others.

356
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:51,120
Everyone thinks the same.

357
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:52,320
- True.
- Really?

358
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,640
- By the way, Maruya.
- Yes?

359
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:56,130
What did you guys discuss at the interview?

360
00:18:56,130 --> 00:18:58,800
I'm Izumi's older brother, Yamato.

361
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:02,740
Don't barge into my life anymore.

362
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:08,000
Well, it was just a casual talk.

363
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:12,020
There's nothing more to ask about an excellent employee.

364
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:14,500
It's because Maruya-kun is our department's ace (top employee).

365
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,900
It's nothing like that.

366
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:17,780
Honestly,

367
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:19,490
I'm more interested in knowing

368
00:19:19,490 --> 00:19:22,510
which one of you submitted your resignation.

369
00:19:22,510 --> 00:19:23,640
It's not me.

370
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,600
- Not me.
- It wasn't me.

371
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,720
What?

372
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,910
None of you?

373
00:19:28,910 --> 00:19:31,730
If that person is not here...

374
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:36,730
[Sales team schedule]

375
00:19:36,730 --> 00:19:38,710
[Sanada: on leave.]

376
00:19:39,550 --> 00:19:42,210
Is it Sanada-san?

377
00:19:42,210 --> 00:19:43,920
I see.

378
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:49,917
It seems the sales department is working really hard.

379
00:19:49,917 --> 00:19:53,420
Somehow, they all became so reliable.

380
00:19:53,420 --> 00:19:56,360
Isn't that because of their boss?

381
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:57,990
You're good at praising people.

382
00:19:57,990 --> 00:19:59,450
It's my honest opinion.

383
00:19:59,450 --> 00:20:03,180
But we have become a good team.

384
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:07,560
Ichinose-kun, the newcomer, comes up with ideas.

385
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:10,380
Maruya-kun leads everyone.

386
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:13,910
And Kaburagi-kin follows up.

387
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,340
Then...

388
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:19,900
there are those parting ways because of new challenges.

389
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:22,810
Feeling lonely?

390
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:25,820
Yes.

391
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,290
Oh, hello.

392
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:51,320
- The other day in Aomori...
- You are

393
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,020
not Kosuke's father, right?
[My Cuteness Is About to Expire!?]

394
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:56,020
- You found out?
- Yes.

395
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,180
I see.

396
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:01,850
Somehow, it's like I deceived you.

397
00:21:01,850 --> 00:21:04,060
You must be upset.

398
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:06,120
I'm sorry about that.

399
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:16,050
I broke up with Maruya-san.

400
00:21:17,340 --> 00:21:19,300
I was reminded of a past I wanted to erase.

401
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:22,490
I got very emotional in front of Maruya-san.

402
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:26,320
I was so unhappy with my narrow mind.

403
00:21:27,030 --> 00:21:29,750
The past will never go away.

404
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:34,600
I wonder how long I'll be here.

405
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,410
I want to go back.

406
00:21:36,410 --> 00:21:38,330
Where do you reside?

407
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:40,370
It's very, very far away.

408
00:21:40,370 --> 00:21:41,491
"Far away"?

409
00:21:41,491 --> 00:21:43,420
Super far.

410
00:21:43,420 --> 00:21:44,900
Outside Japan?

411
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:47,590
It's not about physical distance

412
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:51,070
as it is about time distance.

413
00:21:51,070 --> 00:21:55,160
I came here by accident.

414
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:06,310
Look out.

415
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:30,921
[Nichimai Newspaper]

416
00:22:30,921 --> 00:22:32,790
[April 18, 2022]

417
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:35,700
The year of 2022.

418
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:38,000
And I don't know how to go back.

419
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:42,320
Am I correct in assuming this is a temporary memory loss?

420
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:44,040
I guess it's something like that.

421
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:46,600
I was at a loss,

422
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:50,250
but then I remembered that

423
00:22:50,250 --> 00:22:52,460
I knew one person from way back.

424
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:53,850
That person is Maruya-san?

425
00:22:53,850 --> 00:22:54,790
Yes.

426
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,500
I'm Kosuke Maruya from the sales department.

427
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,730
I couldn't help but brag that

428
00:22:59,730 --> 00:23:02,150
he looked just like my younger self.

429
00:23:02,150 --> 00:23:06,700
All I've been thinking of the past years is work.

430
00:23:07,510 --> 00:23:11,350
But when I saw him, I remembered something.

431
00:23:12,230 --> 00:23:16,170
That's right, there was a time I was in love, too.

432
00:23:17,310 --> 00:23:19,150
"Love"?

433
00:23:20,620 --> 00:23:23,980
If I get home safely, maybe I should see her again.

434
00:23:23,980 --> 00:23:25,920
Meeting the one you loved?

435
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:29,070
Though, I am also a bit ashamed to see her.

436
00:23:44,470 --> 00:23:46,340
I'm back.

437
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:48,200
Thank you for your hard work.

438
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:50,530
What happened?

439
00:23:50,530 --> 00:23:52,380
I can't do this anymore.

440
00:23:52,380 --> 00:23:53,141
What?

441
00:23:53,141 --> 00:23:57,020
We managed to get the data on empty cans and retail sales,

442
00:23:57,020 --> 00:23:59,430
but we just can't seem to keep up with the data analysis.

443
00:23:59,430 --> 00:24:00,800
I was wrong!

444
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:02,200
I didn't realize there were so many retailers!

445
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,880
I told you, right?

446
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:06,970
If you knew, you should have stopped me more forcefully.

447
00:24:06,970 --> 00:24:09,380
Maruya-san, what should we do?

448
00:24:09,380 --> 00:24:12,620
Without the analysis, it is impossible to determine the product's availability,

449
00:24:12,620 --> 00:24:17,000
which means we can't present it at the Executive Committee meeting.

450
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,390
Data analysis...

451
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:20,700
Can we ask Sanada-san to do it?

452
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:24,830
But she's on leave now.

453
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:26,660
And she is going to resign.

454
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:29,570
There are only two days left until the Executive Committee meeting.

455
00:24:30,530 --> 00:24:33,710
I will stay behind and do it.

456
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:35,650
That's right.

457
00:24:35,650 --> 00:24:38,370
Whoever can stay behind, please stay.

458
00:24:38,370 --> 00:24:40,260
- All right.
- Let's do our best.

459
00:25:00,510 --> 00:25:03,390
[Izumi Sanada]

460
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,980
[Izumi Sanada]

461
00:25:29,950 --> 00:25:31,610
Everyone.

462
00:25:31,610 --> 00:25:34,630
Our work efficiency is declining. Why don't we go home for a while?

463
00:25:34,630 --> 00:25:36,470
I agree.

464
00:25:36,470 --> 00:25:41,280
I also can't take it anymore.

465
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,240
I want to take a shower.

466
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:50,360
Thank you for your hard work.

467
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:53,680
Excuse me.

468
00:25:57,870 --> 00:26:00,370
It's about Izumi, isn't it?

469
00:26:00,370 --> 00:26:01,560
Yes.

470
00:26:02,990 --> 00:26:05,580
You must be shocked.

471
00:26:05,580 --> 00:26:07,870
I'm sorry about what happened that day.

472
00:26:07,870 --> 00:26:09,310
It's fine.

473
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:11,390
I did something that was unnecessary.

474
00:26:11,390 --> 00:26:13,340
- I'm sorry about that.
- It's okay.

475
00:26:14,330 --> 00:26:18,950
All I wanted was to make a place for myself.

476
00:26:18,980 --> 00:26:23,540
Izumi-san said she wanted to create a place where she belonged.

477
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,400
Yes.

478
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,900
In the past, we had a lot going in our family.

479
00:26:29,570 --> 00:26:33,900
If you don't mind, can you tell me about it?

480
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:51,410
Izumi and I had always stayed together since we were born.

481
00:26:51,410 --> 00:26:54,750
Because of my outgoing personality,

482
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:56,490
ever since I was a child,

483
00:26:56,490 --> 00:26:59,120
I would be surrounded by people.

484
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:00,860
I was that kind of child.

485
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:02,160
But...

486
00:27:03,140 --> 00:27:05,810
Izumi was different.

487
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:13,500
She's shy and often spent time by herself.

488
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:15,230
Wait a minute.

489
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:19,540
Looking at her like that, as a brother,

490
00:27:19,540 --> 00:27:22,650
I wanted to create a space for her.

491
00:27:22,650 --> 00:27:26,880
But it only resulted in strengthening her sense of isolation.

492
00:27:27,860 --> 00:27:29,450
So...

493
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:35,290
for Izumi, the only place she felt connected was with family.

494
00:27:36,430 --> 00:27:38,460
Upon entering junior high school,

495
00:27:38,460 --> 00:27:43,790
I was admitted to a school in Shizuoka based on sports recommendations.

496
00:27:43,790 --> 00:27:46,620
Our family was planning to move.

497
00:27:46,620 --> 00:27:48,160
However,

498
00:27:49,270 --> 00:27:52,790
only Izumi was adamant about not wanting to go.

499
00:27:52,790 --> 00:27:55,010
I think she didn't want an unfamiliar environment,

500
00:27:55,010 --> 00:27:58,500
and she feared that more than anything.

501
00:27:58,500 --> 00:28:01,460
In the end, I moved to Shizuoka with my father.

502
00:28:01,460 --> 00:28:05,200
My mother and Izumi stayed behind.

503
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:09,930
Not too long after that, our parents divorced.

504
00:28:09,990 --> 00:28:13,510
Of course, it wasn't Izumi's fault.

505
00:28:13,510 --> 00:28:16,890
My parents didn't get along to begin with.

506
00:28:16,890 --> 00:28:19,300
Now I think about it,

507
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:23,280
I believe that's why our mother stayed behind with Izumi.

508
00:28:25,510 --> 00:28:27,160
However,

509
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:32,380
Izumi always thought it was her fault.

510
00:28:32,380 --> 00:28:34,340
She felt her selfish desire

511
00:28:34,340 --> 00:28:36,520
not only ruined the place where she belonged

512
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:39,360
but also ruined our family as well.

513
00:28:40,980 --> 00:28:47,970
A place to be yourself is not available for everyone.

514
00:28:56,670 --> 00:28:58,920
[English textbook]

515
00:29:06,990 --> 00:29:09,930
[Kosuke Maruya]

516
00:29:17,670 --> 00:29:18,770
Yes?

517
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:21,170
Maruya here.

518
00:29:23,390 --> 00:29:24,840
Well...

519
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:26,730
I'm already...

520
00:29:26,730 --> 00:29:30,350
I'm not calling to ask if you want to get back together.

521
00:29:32,780 --> 00:29:37,490
Right now, we're working on the plan Ichinose initiated.

522
00:29:37,490 --> 00:29:39,970
We all worked hard and managed to gather the data, but

523
00:29:39,970 --> 00:29:41,770
we're struggling with it.

524
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:44,210
That's why

525
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:48,130
I hope you can help us, Sanada-san.

526
00:29:51,030 --> 00:29:56,080
We lack ability to analyze the data we collected

527
00:29:56,080 --> 00:30:01,020
and to propose innovative plans based on that analysis.

528
00:30:01,090 --> 00:30:03,470
We need your analytical and proposal skills,

529
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:06,210
that amazed the department chief of Tokusho Corp.

530
00:30:06,210 --> 00:30:08,070
We need you right now.

531
00:30:08,870 --> 00:30:11,280
I need your help

532
00:30:12,460 --> 00:30:15,080
to protect the place where everyone belongs.

533
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:21,650
"The place where everyone belongs."

534
00:30:22,610 --> 00:30:23,820
Yes.

535
00:30:25,550 --> 00:30:27,370
That's all I wanted to say.

536
00:30:28,210 --> 00:30:29,970
Goodbye.

537
00:30:32,060 --> 00:30:34,380
